  - Taking the first and second derivatives of $f$ with respect to $x$, we get

    $$
    \begin{align*}
    f'(x)&=3ax^2+2bx+c\\[12pt]
    f''(x)&=6ax+2b \tag*{\textbf{A1}}\\[-12pt]
    \end{align*}
    $$

    Solving for the inflection point, we get

    $$
    \begin{align*}
    f''(x)&=0 \tag*{\textbf{M1}}\\[12pt]
    6ax+2b&=0\\[12pt]
    x&=-\dfrac{2b}{6a}\\[12pt]
    &=\dfrac{1}{3}\left(-\dfrac{b}{a}\right) \tag*{\textbf{A1}}\\[12pt]
    &\hspace{0.275em}\answer{= \dfrac{x_1+x_2+x_3}{3}}
    \end{align*}
    $$


